    <description>Is it possible to add `cache-control` headers for images when delpoying to Vercel? It doesn&#39;t seem to work out-of-the box with the default [vercel.json](https://docs.frontity.org/deployment/deploy-using-vercel) file from the documentation. image files seem to get a `max-age=0` as `cache-control` header.

What should I add to `vercel.json` to add `cache-control` for files like png, jpg and svg, coming from the wp-content folder?</description>
